IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF HOLDEN VILLAGE, A LUTHERAN MINISTRY, IS TO WELCOME ALL PEOPLE INTO THE WILDERNESS TO BE CALLED, EQUIPPED AND SENT BY GOD AS WE SHARE RHYTHMS OF WORD AND SACRAMENT, WORK, RECREATION AND STUDY, INTERCESSION AND HEALING.
IRS990.Desc: WELCOMING ALL PEOPLE INTO THE WILDERNESS TO BE CALLED, EQUIPPED AND SENT BY GOD AS WE SHARE THE RHYTHMS OF WORD AND SACRAMENT, RECREATION AND STUDY, INTERCESSION AND HEALING. FOR THE FY ENDING 10-31-15 HOLDEN VILLAGE SERVED OVER 3,700 GUESTS. HOLDEN ALSO RECEIVES SUPPORT IN THE FORM OF VOLUNTEER LABOR. FOR THE FY ENDING 10-31-15: 1) 9 VOLUNTEERS PROVIDED SPECIALIZED LABOR WORTH $161,302 TO REMODEL BUILDINGS AND MAINTAIN AGING UTILITY SYSTEMS AND PROVIDE NOURISHING MEALS, 2) SKILLED LABOR (TEACHING STAFF, MEDICS, BOOKKEEPERS, CARPENTERS, ETC.) WORTH $14,505 WHEN COMPUTED AT $26.05/HOUR, 3) COMMON OR "UNSKILLED" LABOR INTEGRAL TO OPERATIONS WORTH $126,172 WHEN COMPUTED AT MINIMUM WAGE. THIS TOTALED 6,192 HOURS OF SKILLED AND 34,785 HOURS OF COMMON LABOR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: HOLDEN VILLAGE OPERATES A BOOKSTORE WHICH PROVIDES BOOKS, RECORDED AND WRITTEN MUSIC, CARDS, CLOTHING ITEMS, CRAFTS, POTTERY, JEWELRY, AND OTHER RESOURCES TO GUESTS, STAFF, AND MINE REMEDIATION WORKERS. RESOURCE MATERIALS ARE IN KEEPING WITH THE HOLDEN MISSION OF HEALING, INTERCESSION, ENVIRONMENTAL STEWARDSHIP, SACRAMENT, AND GOOD HUMOR. IN ADDITION, THE BOOKSTORE SUPPLIES A SMALL AMOUNT OF MERCANTILE GOODS FOR SALE TO GUESTS, STAFF, AND MINE REMEDIATION WORKERS, SUCH AS TOOTHBRUSHES, TOOTHPASTE, CAMPING SUPPLIES, PENS AND PAPER, SNACK ITEMS, ETC.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: IN ADDITION, HOLDEN HAS A VARIETY OF OTHER PROGRAMS THAT OPERATE WITHIN THE OVERALL FUNCTIONING OF THE MISSION AND PURPOSE OF THE VILLAGE, INCLUDING ARTS & CRAFTS, POTTERY, POOL HALL/BOWLING ALLEY, SNACK BAR, ESPRESSO STAND, BOARDING STUDENTS, SPONSORING JAPANESE FOREIGN STUDENTS, AND OTHER MISCELLANEOUS PROGRAM ACTIVITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HOLDEN VILLAGE'S SPENDING POLICY IS SUBJECT TO THE SPENDING POLICY OF THE ELCA ENDOWMENT. THE ELCA ENDOWMENT FUND DISTRIBUTIONS ARE BASED ON A BOARD OF TRUSTEE APPROVED RATE MULTIPLIED BY THE FIVE PREVIOUS YEAR-END UNIT VALUES. ANNUALLY, WITH THE ADOPTION OF THE BUDGET, THE HOLDEN VILLAGE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DETERMINES WHETHER TO TAKE THE ELCA ENDOWMENT FUND DISTRIBUTIONS TO BE USED AS OPERATING INCOME OR TO REINVEST THE DISTRIBUTIONS.
